of Parliament and the Chairman of Safety and Security, Gauteng Mapiti Matsena
has died. Sinoville
cops in the North of Pretoria responded to a call out in Doornpoort. When
they arrived, they found the deceased on the floor in the main bedroom. Following
that paramedics were called to the scene and they declared him dead after
attempts to resuscitate him have failed. Matsena
reportedly went to the toilet when the suspect gained entry through the
unlocked outside glassdoor. According
to the police the suspect allegedly covered the deceased's wife with a blanket,
then the wife ran out and called her son, from the other house on the premises
who witnessed the fight and saw the suspect stabbing his father with an unknown
object in the chest. The
suspect jumped the wall in front of the house on the South-Western side.